cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text encoding using recurrent neural encoders. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses network embedding methods and link prediction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a new method that combines different sources of information using neural networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with encoding textual node descriptors. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper uses two networks derived from UMLS, a biomedical ontology database.
